job_description:
Project Manager - General Contractor - Data Center - Columbus

Highland Consulting Group is a National Executive Recruiting firm that specializes in recruiting top performers in the construction industry.

We are working with a well-established General Contractor in the Columbus, OH area that has an immediate need for an experienced Project Manager. Successful candidates must have a minimum of 5 years’ experience of construction management working with the construction of data centers. This position will complete a new data center from award to closeout. This project has almost a 2-year timeline, and they need someone that has experience in the construction of the space, implementation of all of the equipment, the tie in with several buildings, and the commissioning process. This is an on-site position and provides the chance to work with some of the larger players in this space.

Job Responsibilities Will Include, But Are Not Limited To
• Manages and supervises all phases of assigned projects
• Prepare and manage schedules
• Estimate change orders
• Negotiate all change orders and maintain change order logs
• Manage project budgets and approves all expenses
• Contract Administration
• Buyout of subcontracts & Equipment
• Interface with the owner on all projects assigned
• Assemble and maintain complete project records and close-out documents
• Perform project punch-list inspection(s), in coordination with Superintendents and the owner’s representative, and issue punch list to all relevant subcontractors
• Stay in contact with past clients for repeat work

Job Requirements
• Must have vertical construction experience as well as a history of working Data center projects
• A solid understanding of electrical construction is preferred
• Solid Communication both verbal and written
• Ability to establish timelines and budgets
• Experience in cost estimation and negotiating
• Ability to multi-task
• Ability to lead productive, multi-discipline meetings
• Solid, proven and verifiable record of career stability and project management success a must
• 5+ years’ experience in general construction management with large project exposure
• Bachelor’s degree is preferred but not required
• Candidates with a strong construction background will be strongly considered.

Benefits
• This company cares about and is committed to the wellbeing of its employees and their families. Their commitment is reflected in a comprehensive benefit package provided to all employees.

Confidentiality
• We respect your privacy and will never submit a resume to a third party without your permission. You can be assured that the information you give us will never be forwarded to any company without your specific, direct permission in advance.

Contact
• If you have this type of experience, please apply to this position. You can also contact me directly to learn more about this opportunity.

John Kane

job_description:
Seeking a co-founder/developer who can build this tool (approx 100 hours) in exchange for equity in the business.

This is an UNPAID remote role for an AI + Ecommerce Developer. The AI + Ecommerce Developer will be responsible for building an ecommerce website, including developing responsive web design, AI API integrations, front-end development, software development, and web development.

Qualifications
• E-Commerce and Responsive Web Design skills
• Front-End Development and Software Development skills
• Web Development skills
• Experience with AI-based technologies (APIs) is *necessary*
• Excellent problem solving and analytical skills
• Ability to work independently and remotely

Relevant experience in ecommerce development and familiarity with popular ecommerce platforms and tools would also be beneficial.

We are building a web-based platform designed to allow users to craft unique, one of a kind merchandise inspired by their favorite songs. The tool seamlessly combines the capabilities of a text-to-image generator with advanced API integrations. By simply entering the name of a song, the platform fetches its lyrics and underlying meaning through a API call (Genius API or similar). It then employs these insights to generate custom prompts, creating bespoke images that encapsulate the essence of the song. These images are then seamlessly applied to a wide range of merchandise, using an integration with a leading print-on-demand services, such as Printful.com, and high quality mockups are shown to the user in real time. To ensure a fluid and user-friendly experience, the platform is equipped with all the standard e-commerce functionalities, including an intuitive shopping cart, shipping, and secure payment processing. Prospective developers will need a robust understanding of API integrations, covering both AI-driven services for dynamic content creation and standard e-commerce functionality.

Here is an example of a similar (but without the music theme) site: https://pixite.ai/

Qualifications: E-Commerce and Responsive Web Design skills
Front-End Development and Software Development skills
Web Development skills
Experience with AI-based technologies (APIs) is *necessary*
Excellent problem solving and analytical skills
Ability to work independently and remotely
Relevant experience in ecommerce development and familiarity with popular ecommerce platforms and tools would also be beneficial

job_description:
A pioneer in K–12 education since 2000, Amplify is leading the way in next-generation curriculum and assessment. Our core and supplemental programs in ELA, math, and science engage all students in rigorous learning and inspire them to think deeply, creatively, and for themselves. Our formative assessment products help teachers identify the targeted instruction students need to build a strong foundation in early reading and math. All of our programs provide educators with powerful tools that help them understand and respond to the needs of every student. Today, Amplify serves more than 10 million students in all 50 states. For more information, visit amplify.com.

The Senior Editor, ELA assists the Managing Editor in completing a wide range of editorial projects in both print and digital formats. This higher-level editorial position demands a strong understanding of Amplify's editorial process, platforms, and style, combined with outstanding editorial and writing skills. The Sr Editor often works largely independently and collaborates across teams to manage and complete projects. The Senior Editor takes a high level of responsibility and ownership over ensuring all Amplify ELA materials are extremely accurate, consistent and of a high quality.

Responsibilities Of The Senior Editor
• Manage small projects within larger product;
• Demonstrate knowledge of relationships and connections between ELA products
• Work successfully with other product contributors, including writers, designers, and digital content producers.
• Produce error free copy
• Review lessons independently, as well as those edited by contract editors
• Ensure work reflects editorial guidelines with regards to style, content, and layout
• Copy edit digital and print curriculum and other related materials
• Work closely with writers to understand their intended meaning and improve on the clarity of their text
• Identify inconsistencies and other content problems, and work with writers to fix those problems
• Check the accuracy of direct quotes and details such as page references and material/resource references
• Ensure alignment between student and teacher edition content
• Consult key, in-house, product-specific reference documents (lesson templates, 6–8 and 9–12 Style guides, definitions spreadsheet, terms list, and source text lists) to make sure content aligns with Amplify ELA styles and best practices
• Proofread digital and print files; work with content producers and graphic designers to ensure all content is clean and error-free
• Special projects, as needed

Basic Qualifications Of The Senior Editor, ELA
• Relevant bachelor’s degree
• 4+ years of copy editing experience with a track record of producing clean documents on time
• Advanced understanding of the English language and rules of grammar, punctuation, and other technical aspects of writing
• Excellent communication skills and an ability to work harmoniously with everyone on the curriculum team, including writers, reviewers, graphic designers, and managers
• Extreme attention to detail
• Experience and comfort with an all-digital, remote editing environment
• Ability to work flexibly and independently on multiple projects at the same time, as part of a fast-paced and energetic team
• Availability expected during standard office hours

Preferred Requirements
• Experience with 6–12 English language arts curriculum
• Experience and comfort with all aspects of Google Workspace; experience with various content management systems and other digital platforms

Compensation

The hourly rate range for this role is $45-$48.

We celebrate diversity and are committed to creating an inclusive environment for all employees. To that end, we seek to recruit, develop and retain the most talented people from a diverse candidate pool.

Amplify is an Equal Opportunity Employer of Minorities, Females, Protected Veterans and Individuals with Disabilities.

This position may be funded, in whole or in part, through American Recovery & Reinvestment Act funds.

Amplify Education, Inc. is an E-Verify participant.
